<h2>Rules for using videos</h2>
<ul>
   <li>A <code>title</code> attribute for the <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> must be provided to make the video accessible to users of screen reader software. Including the text '(Video)' at the end  of the title helps to identify the type of content when read out.</li>
   <li>For pre-recorded videos a transcript must be provided to make the content of the video accessible.</li>
   <li>Captions should be included in all videos. Automatically generated captions often need edited and are not as accurate as those written specifically.</li>
   <li>A label <code>&lt;figcaption&gt;</code> may be included to add context to the video.</li>
</ul>
<p>More information on video transcripts and captions is described within <a href="https://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/digital-standards/caption-standards/">caption standards</a>.</p>
